Azure allows integration of private DNS zones with VNets, enabling internal name resolution.

Resources can communicate using domain names instead of IP addresses.

For example, a VM can access a database using a private domain name.

# Real-life use case:
A real-life use case is enterprise applications with internal services.

# Real-life example:
Another example is microservices communicating within a VNet.

Private domains improve manageability and security.
